        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Observation frequency:
We will observe this region in Band 3 in full polarization.
This will ensure all the sample is well within 1/3 of the primary beam.


Sensitivity:
We request a sensitivity of 27 micro-Jy/1" beam. All the samples have been detected and resolved at 345 GHz with 4.5" beam.
The faintest source is SMM1. Its peak intensity is 148 mJy per 4.5" beam at 345 GHz. We estimate the request sensitivity based on this.
The spectral index is assumed to be 3, which is about the typical value of the ISM dust.
The source polarization percentage is assumed to be 1%, which about the typical value we found in dense star forming cores with the SMA.
The polarization intensity will be at least 37 micro-Jy/1". All the other sources are about 2 to 30 times brighter than SMMS1.
We should be able to get an S/N ratio of 1.5 to 45 cross the sample. The fainter sources will be convolved with at least 2" to recover the flux.  

Angular resolution:
We request 1" resolution to resolve the B field within the dense cores.

Proposed pointing:
We propose 7 pointings toward the OMC-3 filament. All the pointings are at the continuum peak.

</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
